9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 542, L.D. 856, “An Act to Phase Out the
10 Income Tax”
11 Amend the bill by striking out all of section 5 and inserting the following:
12 'Sec. 5. 36 MRSA §5111, sub-§8 is enacted to read:
13 8. Income tax eliminated. Beginning January 1, 2030, the imposition of taxes
14 pursuant to this section is prohibited. A return is not required for a taxpayer whose income
15 tax liability has been eliminated under this section.
16 Sec. 6. 36 MRSA §5111, sub-§9 is enacted to read:
17 9. Fiduciary income tax. This section may not be construed to eliminate the
18 imposition of income tax on a fiduciary.
19 Sec. 7. 36 MRSA §5111, sub-§10 is enacted to read:
20 10. Refundable tax credit schedule. Refundable tax credits due to a taxpayer eligible
21 for reduced income tax liability under this section must be reduced in value on the same
22 schedule that tax liability is reduced pursuant to subsection 7.'
23 Amend the bill in section 6 in subsection 1-A in the first line (page 2, line 8 in L.D.)
24 by striking out the following: "2017" and inserting the following: '2018'
25 Amend the bill in section 7 in subsection 7 in the first 2 lines (page 2, lines 33 and 34
26 in L.D.) by striking out the following: "and ending before January 1, 2030"
27 Amend the bill by striking out all of section 8 and inserting the following:
28 'Sec. 8. 36 MRSA §5200, sub-§8 is enacted to read:
29 8. Income tax eliminated. Beginning on or after January 1, 2030, no taxes are
30 imposed under this section. A return is not required for a taxpayer whose income tax
31 liability has been eliminated under this section.
32 Sec. 9. 36 MRSA §5200, sub-§9 is enacted to read:
