7 Amend the bill by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or section
8 number to read consecutively.
9 SUMMARY
1100 This amendment eliminates the requirement for taxpayers to file once their income tax
1111 liability has been reduced to zero. The amendment specifies that the income tax imposed
1122 on fiduciaries is not phased out. The amendment phases out refundable tax credits to
1133 individuals and corporations on the same schedule that income tax liability is phased out
1144 to those taxpayers. The amendment clarifies certain dates as they relate to corporate
1155 income tax filers.
